Soft Baked Oatmeal Chocolate Bars

1/4 c melted coconut oil
3/4 c almond butter
3 tbsp ground flaxseed
1 medium ripe banana, mashed
1/4 c honey
1 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp salt
1 c old fashioned oats, ground
1/2 c semisweet chocolate chips, divided
1/4 c chopped pecans
1/4 c dried tart cherries
1/4 c unsweetened shredded coconut

Preheat oven to 350F. Coat 8" square pan with small amount of coconut oil or cooking spray. In large bowl, mix together coconut oil, almond butter, flaxseed, banana, and honey. Stir in baking powder, salt, oats, and 1/4 c chocolate chips. Pour batter into pan and spread evenly. Top with remaining 1/4 c chocolate chips, pecans, cherries, and coconut. Bake for 25 min, allow to cool for 45 min before slicing into 16 bars.


Nutrition:
Serving size: 1 bar
Calories: 191
Total fat: 13g
Saturated fat: 5g
Monounsaturated fat: 1g
Cholesterol: 0mg
Sodium: 68mg
Carbohydrate: 17g
Dietary fiber: 3g
Sugar: 9g
Protein: 4g
Potassium: 62mg
Iron: 15%
Vitamin C: 1%
Calcium: 5%
